---
/**
 * * About section
 */

import kevinBioImg from "../../assets/images/kevin-bio.jpeg";
import jesseBioImg from "../../assets/images/jesse-bio-img.jpg";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
---

<section id='about' class='site-container scroll-mt-10 py-8 md:py-12'>
	<h2 class='h2 text-primary-500 staatliches-regular py-4 text-center text-pretty uppercase'>
		Meet our crew
	</h2>
	<div class='flex flex-col-reverse md:flex-row'>
		<div class='md:mt-6 md:w-2/3'>
			<h3 class='h2 staatliches-regular place-content-center py-4 text-center'>Jesse Worstell</h3>
			<div class='bg-base-100 p-8 md:mt-8 md:mb-20 lg:text-lg'>
				<p class='py-2'>
					Jesse began playing guitar when he was 14. His first lessons were taught to him by
					friends, jamming after school and on weekends. 30+ years later, he&apos;s still playing,
					writing, teaching, and learning.
				</p>
				<p class='py-2'>
					His love of music and creating has taken him across the country, sharing the stage with
					Bon Jovi, Cage the Elephant, Candlebox, Yo Gabba Gabba, and more.
				</p>
				<p class='py-2'>
					After touring for most of the late 90s and early 2000s, he has been teaching guitar to
					students of all ages since 2013. He continues to write and perform in various projects and
					bands in the Hi-Desert.
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class='mr-auto max-w-md md:w-1/3 md:max-w-none'>
			<div class='my-auto aspect-[3/4] w-full overflow-hidden'>
				<Image
					src={jesseBioImg}
					alt='Jesse Worstell'
					width={450}
					densities={[1.5, 2]}
					class='h-auto min-h-full w-full min-w-full object-cover'
				/>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class='flex flex-col md:flex-row'>
		<div class='mr-auto max-w-md md:w-1/3 md:max-w-none'>
			<div class='my-auto mt-4 aspect-[3/4] w-full overflow-hidden'>
				<Image
					src={kevinBioImg}
					alt='Kevin Zieber'
					width={450}
					densities={[1.5, 2]}
					class='h-auto min-h-full w-full min-w-full object-cover'
				/>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class='md:mt-6 md:w-2/3'>
			<h3 class='h2 staatliches-regular place-content-center py-4 text-center'>Kevin Zieber</h3>
			<div class='bg-base-100 p-8 md:mt-8 md:mb-20 lg:text-lg'>
				<p class='py-2'>
					Kevin has been playing in bands for over 20 years, spanning punk, metal, rock, folk, and
					everything in between. A lifelong student of music, Kevin started off playing the trombone
					in junior high before finding his way to the guitar and the drums.
				</p>
				<p class='py-2'>
					In addition to his time at The Noise Floor, Kevin is a teaching artist with Groundwork
					Arts. Every week, he teaches an afterschool music program in the Morongo Basin sharing his
					love and joy in music with local elementary students
				</p>
				<p class='py-2'>
					Music has given Kevin the means to communicate, express, and connect with so many
					musicians from all walks of life all across the country. His greatest love is sharing
					music with others and teaching.
				</p>
				<!-- <div class='flex w-3/4 justify-end'>
					<p class='font-heading-1 comfortaa-regular text-3xl italic'>- Kevin</p>
				</div> -->
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

<!-- Mission statement

Between Kevin and Jesse, we have 50 years of experience practicing, learning, playing, and touring with musicians from all walks of life all across the country. Beyond our shared lifelong love of music, we are also united by a deep reverence and respect for the art of teaching, instruction, and sharing music with the people around us. Nothing is more important to us than community, and our dream is to help the community grow, exchange, and express itself through music. Nothing brings strangers together like music, and our goal is to provide a space where musicians can come together, play together, learn from each other, and get the things they need to be their most creative and expressive.
-->
